    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Waistcoats that are woven, usually woolen, and that open the full length of the center front. An example is the short woollen waistcoat with sleeves, formerly part of the garrison uniform worn by U.S. and British troops ca. WWI.</Note_Text>
